Author:
Vol / Page: 228
Edition:
Quote: It is necessary to hold each lot of sheep in the bath for the time necessary to secure thorough immersion. This may be done ... by the use of the crutch.
Notes:  [OED2]

Date: 7/10/1933
Source: Press, The
Author:
Vol / Page: 15
Edition:
Quote: <i>Crutch</i>. (1) to cut away the wool round a sheep's tail and hind legs so that he will not foul himself. (2) When sheep are dipped they are shoved under with a thing like an inverted <i>crutch</i>. This is called <i>crutching</i>. (3) The implement used for (2). (C.) Implement used for crutching sheep [in the dip].
Notes: (Acland Gloss.)

